# Developmental prosopagnosics have normal spatial integration in posterior ventral face-selective regions

## Overview

Here we provide the raw fMRI responses from the paper *[Developmental
prosopagnosics have normal spatial integration in posterior ventral face-
selective regions](paperlink)* (Daniel A. Stehr, Yiyuan Zhang, Anusha Patgiri, Alexis Kidder,
Kendrick N. Kay, Bradley C. Duchaine)

Each participant underwent two fMRI data collection sessions. The first session
consisted of an anatomical (T1w) scan and four runs of a multi-category
localizer used to define face- and scene-selective regions. The second
session consisted of five runs of a population receptive field (pRF) mapping
experiment used to define V1, V2, V3, hV4 and estimate pRF properties in all
category-selective regions.

The file *used_mri_sequences.pdf* contains technical details regarding the MRI
sequences used.

The code used for preprocessing and analyzing the fMRI data is available on
[GitHub][github].

## Analysis
Code for performing the preprocessing of the raw fMRI data and fitting population receptive fields is available [here](https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/Population_Receptive_Field_Properties_in_Developmental_Prosopagnosics_and_Controls/29582888).

## Contact

For any questions regarding the project data or code you can get in touch with
Daniel Stehr (daniel.a.stehr@dartmouth.edu)

